<item>
            <title>[LU-2036] sanity.sh test_76: fails with lod/osp (inodes are not purged as expected)</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2036</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;OSP objects are not removed immediately, so ll_d_iput() in unlink path finds extent locks and do not reset nlink to 0 leaving the inode in the cache.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;we need to figure out another way to purge inode...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;on MDS corresponding inode does get nlink=0 only if the inode is actually being destroyed (orphans get nlink=1 being on PENDING/). this zero nlink propagated to the client can be a signal for ELC on the client ?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
